hh3cDlswExt.name: hh3cDlswExt

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

hh3cDlswExt.contactinfo: Platform Team Hangzhou H3C Tech. Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.h3c.com Zip:100085
hh3cDlswExt.description: The MIB module for management of H3C specific Data Link Switching protocol enhancements. DLSw is described in RFC 1795, RFC 2024 and RFC2166.

hh3cdeNodeVendorID.name: hh3cdeNodeVendorID
hh3cdeNodeVendorID.description: The value identifies the manufacturer's IEEE-assigned Organizationally Unique Identifier (OUI) of this DLSw. This information is reported in DLSw Capabilities Exchange.

hh3cdeNodeIpAddrType.name: hh3cdeNodeIpAddrType
hh3cdeNodeIpAddrType.description: The type of ip address: IPv4 or IPv6.

hh3cdeNodeLocalAddr.name: hh3cdeNodeLocalAddr
hh3cdeNodeLocalAddr.description: Local peer ip address. This ip address must have been configured for a port on the router. If no local peer ip address is configured, then this object will be the empty string.

hh3cdeNodePriority.name: hh3cdeNodePriority
hh3cdeNodePriority.description: Peer priority advertised to remote peers in the DLSw Capabilities Exchange. If an end station can reach through more than one peer, the priority of each peer will be considered when a circuit is established. A lower priority indicates that peer will be the preferred choice if there are more than one path to the destination. A value of 65535 indicates the value is meaningless.

hh3cdeNodeInitPacingWindow.name: hh3cdeNodeInitPacingWindow
hh3cdeNodeInitPacingWindow.description: Initial pacing window size. This is the starting size of the pacing window. DLSw uses an adaptive pacing flow control algorithm that automatically adjusts to congestion levels in the network. Pacing windows are used to control how many packets may be sent to a peer before acknowlegement. A value of 65535 indicates the value is meaningless.

hh3cdeNodeMaxPacingWindow.name: hh3cdeNodeMaxPacingWindow
hh3cdeNodeMaxPacingWindow.description: Maximum pacing window size. This is the largest size that the pacing window will grow to. DLSw uses an adaptive pacing flow control algorithm that automatically adjusts to congestion levels in the network. Pacing windows are used to control how many packets may be sent to a peer before acknowlegement.

hh3cdeNodeKeepAliveInterval.name: hh3cdeNodeKeepAliveInterval
hh3cdeNodeKeepAliveInterval.description: Default remote peer keepalive interval in seconds. The keepalive parameter refers to how often DLSw peers send peer keep alives to each other. These periodic messages allow DLSw to keep track of the state of all peers. If set to zero, no keepalives are sent. A value of 65535 indicates the value is meaningless.

hh3cdeNodePermitDynamic.name: hh3cdeNodePermitDynamic
hh3cdeNodePermitDynamic.description: To accept connections from non-configured remote peer when permitDynamic is specified.

hh3cdeNodeConfigSapList.name: hh3cdeNodeConfigSapList
hh3cdeNodeConfigSapList.description: The SAP list indicates which SAPs are allowed. Only SAPs with even numbers are represented, in the form of the most significant bit of the first octet representing the SAP 0, the next most significant bit representing the SAP 2, to the least significant bit of the last octet representing the SAP 254. Data link switching is allowed for those SAPs which have one in its corresponding bit, not allowed otherwise. The whole SAP list has to be changed together. Changing the SAP list affects only new circuit establishments and has no effect on established circuits. This list can be used to restrict specific partners from knowing about all the SAPs used by DLSw on all its interfaces (these are represented in hh3cdeIfSapList for each interface). For instance, one may want to run NetBIOS with some partners but not others. If a node supports sending run-time capabilities exchange messages, changes to this object should cause that action. When to start the run-time capabilities exchange is implementation-specific. The DEFVAL below indicates support for SAPs 0, 2, 4, 6, 8, A, C and E.

hh3cdeNodeMaxTransmission.name: hh3cdeNodeMaxTransmission
hh3cdeNodeMaxTransmission.description: The maximum retry times for TCP packet. Default value is 5.

hh3cdeNodeMulticastStatus.name: hh3cdeNodeMulticastStatus
hh3cdeNodeMulticastStatus.description: Multicast support status. It is disabled by default.

hh3cdeNodeMulticastAddress.name: hh3cdeNodeMulticastAddress
hh3cdeNodeMulticastAddress.description: Multicast address. Default is 224.0.10.0. When the hh3cdeNodeMulticastStatus is disabled, the multicast address is reset to 0.0.0.0.

hh3cdeNodeResetTcpAll.name: hh3cdeNodeResetTcpAll
hh3cdeNodeResetTcpAll.description: Reset all TCP circuit switch. Any return value is meaningless.

hh3cdeNodeStCapTcpNum.name: hh3cdeNodeStCapTcpNum
hh3cdeNodeStCapTcpNum.description: Tcp number reported in DLSw Capabilities Exchange.

hh3cdeNodeTcpQueueMax.name: hh3cdeNodeTcpQueueMax
hh3cdeNodeTcpQueueMax.description: The max length of TCP queue.

hh3cdeTConnConfigTable.name: hh3cdeTConnConfigTable
hh3cdeTConnConfigTable.description: This table defines the peer transport connections that will be initiated or accepted by this DLSw. This table augments dlswTConnConfigTable.

hh3cdeTConnConfigEntry.name: hh3cdeTConnConfigEntry
hh3cdeTConnConfigEntry.description: A list of objects that define specific configuration for a DLSw peer transport connection.

hh3cdeTConnConfigVersion.name: hh3cdeTConnConfigVersion
hh3cdeTConnConfigVersion.description: This value identifies which version (first octet) and release (second octet) of the DLSw standard is supported by this partner DLSw. This information is obtained from a DLSw Capabilities Exchange message received from the partner DLSw. A string of zero length is returned before a Capabilities Exchange message is received, or if one is never received. A conceptual row with a hh3cdeTConnOperState of 'connected' but a zero length partner version indicates that the partner is a non-standard DLSw partner. If an implementation chooses to keep hh3cdeTConnOperEntrys in the 'disconnected' state, this value should remain unchanged.

hh3cdeTConnConfigBackup.name: hh3cdeTConnConfigBackup
hh3cdeTConnConfigBackup.description: The current remote peer is configured as the backup of another configured remote peer.

hh3cdeTConnConfigBackupTAddr.name: hh3cdeTConnConfigBackupTAddr
hh3cdeTConnConfigBackupTAddr.description: It is the ip address of a configured remote peer of which the current remote peer is configrued as backup.

hh3cdeTConnOperTable.name: hh3cdeTConnOperTable
hh3cdeTConnOperTable.description: A list of peer transport connections. Each connected peer will create a conceptual row in the table. When the peer disconnects, the row will be deleted from the table. This table augments dlswTConnOperTable.

hh3cdeTConnOperEntry.name: hh3cdeTConnOperEntry
hh3cdeTConnOperEntry.description: A list of objects that contain spefific operational information for a DLSw peer transport connection.

hh3cdeTConnOperPeerType.name: hh3cdeTConnOperPeerType
hh3cdeTConnOperPeerType.description: The current remote peer is configured when the value is 'configured'.

hh3cdeTConnOperVendorID.name: hh3cdeTConnOperVendorID
hh3cdeTConnOperVendorID.description: The value identifies the manufacturer's IEEE-assigned Organizationally Unique Identifier (OUI) of remote peer.

hh3cdeTConnOperVersionString.name: hh3cdeTConnOperVersionString
hh3cdeTConnOperVersionString.description: Version information of remote peer. The length up to 512 bytes.

hh3cdeTConnOperUpTime.name: hh3cdeTConnOperUpTime
hh3cdeTConnOperUpTime.description: The amount of time (in seconds) since this transport connection last entered the 'connected' state.

hh3cdeTConnOperMulticastAddress.name: hh3cdeTConnOperMulticastAddress
hh3cdeTConnOperMulticastAddress.description: When remote peer supports DLSw2.0, this node identifies its multicast address.

hh3cdeTConnOperStCapTcpNumber.name: hh3cdeTConnOperStCapTcpNumber
hh3cdeTConnOperStCapTcpNumber.description: Number of tcp supported when capabilities exchanging.

hh3cdeTConnOperRecvPkts.name: hh3cdeTConnOperRecvPkts
hh3cdeTConnOperRecvPkts.description: The number of Switch-to-Switch Protocol (SSP) messages received on this tcp transport connection.

hh3cdeTConnOperSendPkts.name: hh3cdeTConnOperSendPkts
hh3cdeTConnOperSendPkts.description: The number of SSP messages sent on this tcp transport connection.

hh3cdeTConnOperDropPkts.name: hh3cdeTConnOperDropPkts
hh3cdeTConnOperDropPkts.description: The number of SSP messages dropped on this tcp transport connection.

hh3cdeTConnTcpConfigTable.name: hh3cdeTConnTcpConfigTable
hh3cdeTConnTcpConfigTable.description: This table defines the TCP transport connections that will be either initiated by or accepted by this DSLw. It augments the entries in dlswTConnConfigTable whose domain is dlswTCPDomain. In other words for each conceptual row in the dlswTConnConfigTable, if the dlswTConnConfigTDomain is dlswTCPDomain, that conceptual row will be augmented by this table. dlswTCPDomain, dlswTConnConfigTable, and dlswTConnConfigTDomain are all imported from DLSW-MIB (RFC 2024). This table augments dlswTConnTcpConfigTable.

hh3cdeTConnTcpConfigEntry.name: hh3cdeTConnTcpConfigEntry
hh3cdeTConnTcpConfigEntry.description: A list of objects that define specific configuration for a DLSw peer transport connection within the dlswTCPDomain. dlswTCPDomain is imported from DLSW-MIB (RFC 2024).

hh3cdeTConnTcpConfigQueueMax.name: hh3cdeTConnTcpConfigQueueMax
hh3cdeTConnTcpConfigQueueMax.description: Maximum output TCP queue size for this remote peer. For DLSw over TCP encapsulation, packets may be queued due to congestion of the TCP network. This variable is used to set the output queue maximum of the underlying TCP connection for the peer represented by the conceptual row.

hh3cdeBridgeTable.name: hh3cdeBridgeTable
hh3cdeBridgeTable.description: A list of bridge group which is serving for DLSw.

hh3cdeBridgeNumIndex.name: hh3cdeBridgeNumIndex
hh3cdeBridgeNumIndex.description: This value identifies the bridge number.

hh3cdeBridgeIfTable.name: hh3cdeBridgeIfTable
hh3cdeBridgeIfTable.description: The list of interface on which DLSw is active.

hh3cdeBridgeIfEntry.name: hh3cdeBridgeIfEntry
hh3cdeBridgeIfEntry.description: The list of bridge interface information.

hh3cdeBridgeIfBrgGrp.name: hh3cdeBridgeIfBrgGrp
hh3cdeBridgeIfBrgGrp.description: This value identifies the bridge number attached to the interface.

hh3cdeQllcTable.name: hh3cdeQllcTable
hh3cdeQllcTable.description: The table defines attributes related for those QLLC that participate in data link switching.

hh3cdeQllcEntry.name: hh3cdeQllcEntry
hh3cdeQllcEntry.description: The ifIndex belongs to the interface which link protocol is x.25.

hh3cQllcLocalMac.name: hh3cQllcLocalMac
hh3cQllcLocalMac.description: The virtual MAC address used to represent the QLLC-attached link station to the rest of the DLSw network.

hh3cQllcLocalSap.name: hh3cQllcLocalSap
hh3cQllcLocalSap.description: The SAP used to represent this link station.

hh3cQllcRemoteMac.name: hh3cQllcRemoteMac
hh3cQllcRemoteMac.description: The MAC address to which DLSw should attempt to connect this link station. If this information is not available, a length of zero for this object should be returned.

hh3cQllcRemoteSap.name: hh3cQllcRemoteSap
hh3cQllcRemoteSap.description: The SAP of the remote station to which this link station should be connected. If this information is not available, a length of zero for this object should be returned.

hh3cdeSdlcPortTable.name: hh3cdeSdlcPortTable
hh3cdeSdlcPortTable.description: The table defines parameters for the interfaces whose link protocol is SDLC.

hh3cdeSdlcPortMaxTransmission.name: hh3cdeSdlcPortMaxTransmission
hh3cdeSdlcPortMaxTransmission.description: Number of times to retry an operation.

hh3cdeSdlcPortTimerACK.name: hh3cdeSdlcPortTimerACK
hh3cdeSdlcPortTimerACK.description: Time to wait for a reply to a frame.

hh3cdeSdlcPortTimerLifeTime.name: hh3cdeSdlcPortTimerLifeTime
hh3cdeSdlcPortTimerLifeTime.description: Time to wait for a reply used by secondary station.

hh3cdeSdlcPortTimerPollPause.name: hh3cdeSdlcPortTimerPollPause
hh3cdeSdlcPortTimerPollPause.description: Time between polls for each secondary SDLC station.

hh3cdeLlc2PortTable.name: hh3cdeLlc2PortTable
hh3cdeLlc2PortTable.description: This table defines parameters for the Ethernet interface.

hh3cdeLlc2PortMaxAck.name: hh3cdeLlc2PortMaxAck
hh3cdeLlc2PortMaxAck.description: Maximum of I-frames received before ACK.

hh3cdeLlc2PortReceiveWindow.name: hh3cdeLlc2PortReceiveWindow
hh3cdeLlc2PortReceiveWindow.description: Maximum number of I-frames to send before received ACK.

hh3cdeLlc2PortTimerAck.name: hh3cdeLlc2PortTimerAck
hh3cdeLlc2PortTimerAck.description: Waiting for ACK time after sending an I-frame.

hh3cdeLlc2PortTimerAckDelay.name: hh3cdeLlc2PortTimerAckDelay
hh3cdeLlc2PortTimerAckDelay.description: Maximum time allows I-frames incoming without replay ACK.

hh3cdeLlc2PortTimerBusy.name: hh3cdeLlc2PortTimerBusy
hh3cdeLlc2PortTimerBusy.description: Waiting time while other LLC2 station is in busy state.

hh3cdeLlc2PortTimerPoll.name: hh3cdeLlc2PortTimerPoll
hh3cdeLlc2PortTimerPoll.description: Waiting time after a P frame is sent.

hh3cdeLlc2PortTimerReject.name: hh3cdeLlc2PortTimerReject
hh3cdeLlc2PortTimerReject.description: Waiting time after a REJ frame is sent.

hh3cdeRchCacheNextIndex.name: hh3cdeRchCacheNextIndex
hh3cdeRchCacheNextIndex.description: The next value of hh3cdeRchCacheIndex to be assigned by the agent. A retrieval of this object atomically reserves the returned value for use by the manager to create a row in hh3cdeRchCacheTable. This makes it possible for the agent to control the index space of the MAC address cache, yet allows the manager to administratively create new rows.

hh3cdeRchCacheStatus.name: hh3cdeRchCacheStatus
hh3cdeRchCacheStatus.description: Current status of reachable cache entry.

hh3cdeRchCacheRemainTime.name: hh3cdeRchCacheRemainTime
hh3cdeRchCacheRemainTime.description: Remain time of reachable cache entry.

hh3cdeRchCacheMac.name: hh3cdeRchCacheMac
hh3cdeRchCacheMac.description: MAC address of reachable cache entry.

hh3cdeRchCacheRemoteIp.name: hh3cdeRchCacheRemoteIp
hh3cdeRchCacheRemoteIp.description: Remote peer ip address of reachable cache entry.

hh3cdeEBMacMapNextIndex.name: hh3cdeEBMacMapNextIndex
hh3cdeEBMacMapNextIndex.description: The next value of hh3cdeEBMacMapIndex to be assigned by the agent. A retrieval of this object atomically reserves the returned value for use by the manager to create a row in hh3cdeEBMacMapTable. This makes it possible for the agent to control the index space of the MAC mapping tables, yet allows the manager to administratively create new rows.

hh3cdeEBIfTable.name: hh3cdeEBIfTable
hh3cdeEBIfTable.description: Information of interface which works for DLSw Ethernet redundancy.

hh3cdeEBIfEntry.name: hh3cdeEBIfEntry
hh3cdeEBIfEntry.description: Parameters defined for DLSw Ethernet redundancy interface.

hh3cdeEBMulticastMac.name: hh3cdeEBMulticastMac
hh3cdeEBMulticastMac.description: Multicast MAC address configured for the Ethernet redundancy of dlsw module. When Ethernet redundancy is inactive, its value is '000000000000'H. To active Ethernet redundancy, give it a valid multicast MAC address.

hh3cdeEBPriority.name: hh3cdeEBPriority
hh3cdeEBPriority.description: Priority configured for the Ethernet redundancy of DLSw module.

hh3cdeEBtimer.name: hh3cdeEBtimer
hh3cdeEBtimer.description: Timer for the Ethernet redundancy of DLSw module.

hh3cdeEBMacMapIndex.name: hh3cdeEBMacMapIndex
hh3cdeEBMacMapIndex.description: Index of MAC address mapping entry.

hh3cdeEBMacMapLocalMac.name: hh3cdeEBMacMapLocalMac
hh3cdeEBMacMapLocalMac.description: Local MAC address in MAC address mapping. When creating a new conceptual row, hh3cdeEBMacMapLocalMac and hh3cdeEBMacMapRemoteMac should be set simultaneously.

hh3cdeEBMacMapRemoteMac.name: hh3cdeEBMacMapRemoteMac
hh3cdeEBMacMapRemoteMac.description: Remote MAC address of MAC address mapping. When creating a new conceptual row, hh3cdeEBMacMapLocalMac and hh3cdeEBMacMapRemoteMac should be set simultaneously.

hh3cdeEBMacMapRowStatus.name: hh3cdeEBMacMapRowStatus
hh3cdeEBMacMapRowStatus.description: Status of MAC address mapping entry.
